</h3><p class="sc-kHOZwM oQMan pf-21_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">First aid kits are a fundamental part of health and safety procedures, providing the necessary tools to address accidents immediately. The Health and Safety (First-Aid) Regulations 1981 mandate that all workplaces must have appropriate first-aid provisions. According to Health and Safety Executive (HSE) guidelines, the average workplace accident rate in the UK is significantly reduced when effective first-aid resources are accessible, underscoring the importance of compliance and proper first aid training.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-iqseJM ducrfW pf-23_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-24_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bTfYFJ fFWOZc pf-25_ pf-heading-1-h3">Understanding key definitions and regulations</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-27_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-28_ pf-text-1"><strong>First aid kit </strong>- A collection of supplies and equipment used to give medical treatment.
